In all the countries that fastjet is present, the airline matched its Tanzanian timekeeping with a 93 per cent aggregate network punctuality. Fastjet operated more than 900 flights in February. “Reliability is one of the cornerstones of customer service for any airline,” said Fastjet Tanzania spokesperson, Ms Lucy Mbogoro. “Fastjet’s pursuit of constant and never-ending improvement across every aspect of our business ultimately comes together under one single minded objective; to deliver affordable and dependable air travel to our clients.” Fastjet connects major domestic centres in Tanzania as well as to key markets in Harare and Lusaka